error.signature: error TS6133: 'x' is declared but its value is never read

verdict.summary: Unused variable or import. TypeScript reports this when noUnusedLocals/noUnusedParameters is enabled.

dead_ends.why_fails: Disables a useful lint rule across the entire project

workarounds.action: Remove the unused variable or import

frequently_confused_with.distinction: 'error TS6133' is a lint_error error while 'error TS18046' has a different failure mode despite similar symptoms. Check error message details to differentiate.
